  "body": "# Description \r\n\r\nWhen running a node via `hardhat node`, then running a deployment script using the `contractFactory`, the result returns an address that the contracts are allegedly deployed. \r\n\r\nWhen querying the deployed contracts from within the deployment script, the data returns as expected, as well when creating a new ethers provider manually then querying via this new provider.\r\n\r\nHowever when attempting to query the same contacts via Remix, with the same contracts, same optimization, the queries return nil values (string empty, addresses zero etc) \r\n\r\nThis is also the case when querying via a TS app, call failures & gas estimation errors\r\n\r\n# Environment\r\n\r\nNode version: v16.13.8\r\nYarn: 1.22.17\r\nOS: Manjaro - Kernel version: 5.15.12-1\r\nSolidity version: 0.8.11 & 0.8.9\r\n\r\n### Hardhat repo\r\n\r\n```\r\n    \"hardhat\": \"^2.8.2\",\r\n    \"hardhat-gas-reporter\": \"^1.0.4\",\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nI've run the same deployment script & remix contracts against a ganache (^7.0.0) instance with solidity v0.8.11 and the contracts & calls are working as expected",
